featured_reviews.review_id: Nice to visit if you continue the walk around this area. You cannot miss the Mosque which is named after the Andalusian saint Ahmed El-Mursi Abul-Abbas, who is highly revered in the region. The mosque is known for its stunning architecture, blending Islamic and Andalusian styles, and its towering minarets.

featured_reviews.review_id: Mosque at Alexandria. I'm not muslim and I had never been in a mosque, but I liked. If it's part of your itinerary in Alexandria, take a look.

featured_reviews.review_id: Beautiful mosque and the most notable and important one in Alexandria, the mosque has the Burial site of numerous Islamic saints and it holds a historical importance of the Islamic heritage of the city, the architecture of the mosque and the whole complex is very beautiful and has this Cairo-Mamluk style of design, the interior design is also beautiful, unfortunately the complex itself is not well-taken care of and signs of neglect are present all around the whole complex, the staff there aren't the nicest at all, they told us not to take pics and then when we were going out of the mosque they asked audaciously for money, underneath the mosque there is a shops complex that's unfortunately dirty and not clean at all, if the whole complex had the care it deserves then the place would be amazing, but for right now i can't really recommend visiting it as it's not that worthy at all.

featured_reviews.review_id:
What a stunning mosque! The outside is so beautiful!

We had a very lame tour that didn't take us to the mosque, but we convinced the guide to take us at least to see it from the outside.

We spent just a couple of minutes there and it was delicious to see it, such a beautiful building. It is a must see
